data.title: DUO: Spectra of diatomic molecules
data.name: Duo
data.description: Duo is a diatomic code for solving a fully coupled rovibronic Schroedinger equation

evidence: "Duo is a diatomic Fortran 2003 code code for solving a fully coupled rovibronic Schroedinger equation" (domain-specific scientific computation, used directly for calculations).

README describes scientific features and bug fixes ("dipole intensity calculations have been optimised", "compute intensities for bound and continuum spectra") but does not mention being a library imported by other software, suggesting a standalone research code.
No installation via package managers, containers, or binaries is mentioned; only the code and documentation are referenced, implying distribution primarily via the source repository and docs link.
